verbose_text: Moreover, upregulation of miR-26a and -26 b results in a decreased expression of most c-MYC target genes, suggesting that miR-26 family can inhibit ESCC cell proliferation via suppression of MYCBP and subsequent inhibition of the c-MYC pathway.
evidence: miR-26 family can inhibit ESCC cell proliferation via suppression of MYCBP
